00:04:26.820 --> 00:04:31.980
And therefore, a Fermi golden
rule arose by integration.

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:35.550
Here, what are we to integrate?

00:04:35.550 --> 00:04:38.040
Well, there is
something to integrate.

00:04:38.040 --> 00:04:41.190
The fact of the
matter is that when

00:04:41.190 --> 00:04:44.340
you have this
black-body radiation,

00:04:44.340 --> 00:04:53.550
you will have a spectrum,
omega, of electric fields.

00:04:53.550 --> 00:04:56.650
You don't just have
one electric field

00:04:56.650 --> 00:04:58.760
at one specific frequency.

00:04:58.760 --> 00:05:03.980
You will have many components
of the electric field

00:05:03.980 --> 00:05:07.830
at different frequencies
at different directions.

00:05:07.830 --> 00:05:10.280
So in particular, when you
have a black-body over this,

00:05:10.280 --> 00:05:19.130
you will have, in this
spectrum, here is omega ba.

00:05:19.130 --> 00:05:26.760
